Kim Jong Il Sends Congratulations to Syrian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il Monday sent a congratulatory message to Bashar Al-Assad, regional secretary of the Arab Baath Socialist Party and president of Syria.
 The message said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I extend warm congratulations to you on your 41st birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Syrian Arab people have made positive efforts to firmly defend the sovereignty and dignity of the country and seek a just and comprehensive solution to the Mideast issue despite difficulties under the guidance of you and your leadership and achieved great successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing satisfaction over the fact that the friendly and cooperative relations between our two countries have invariably developed on good terms even under the complicated international situation, I sincerely wish you good health and happiness and fresh success in your noble work.

Joint Seminar of Juche Idea Study Groups in India Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- A joint seminar on "Juche idea and Songun idea and their vitality" was held by Juche idea study organizations of India in Ghaziabad on Sept. 4 on the occasion of the 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK.
 Present there were Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, Harish Gupta, secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, heads of Juche idea study organizations and adherents to the Juche idea of Delhi, Meerut and Shambhu Dayal universities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the DPRK ambassador to India and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director general of the IIJI in his keynote report said that the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung is one based on the philosophical principle that man is the master of everything and decides everything. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea serves as a guiding idea in the era of independence as it shows the people the way of carving out their destiny and indicates the way of accomplishing the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Truth, scientific accuracy and vitality of the Juche idea have been proven in the long-drawn struggle of the Korean people to achieve independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun idea and Songun politics of the DPRK are based on the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality of the DPRK clearly proves the justice and vitality of the Juche idea and the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is thanks to the Songun politics that the DPRK, though not a big country, has always emerged victorious in the stand-off with the U.S. styling itself "only superpower." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Heads of various Juche idea study organizations in their speeches explained and proved the philosophical principle and scientific accuracy of the Juche idea and the justice and great vitality of the Songun idea and Songun politics and evinced their resolution to intensify the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and Songun idea and boost international solidarity with the Korean people in their just cause.

Meeting Held in India to Hear Report from Scholars Delegation on Its DPRK Visit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held in Ghaziabad, India, on Sept. 2 to hear a report from the Indian delegation of scholars studying the Juche idea on its visit to the DPRK.
 Present there were Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, Harish Gupta, secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, members of the delegation, teachers, employees and students of Delhi, Meerut and Shambu Dayal universities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the DPRK ambassador to India and an embassy official. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting said that they got an unforgettable impression of the DPRK, adding that the DPRK, though not a big country, is a great country as its people are inspired by the great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have profound reverence for President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, they stressed, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wherever we went we were deeply impressed to see the Korean people devotedly working to eternally glorify the leadership feats of the great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During our visit we keenly realized the justice and invincible vitality of the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il and the might of the single-mindedly united Korean people. The U.S. and other allied forces of imperialism are desperately working to isolate and stifle socialist Korea but they can never bring the Korean people to their knees. This is because they are wisely led by Kim Jong Il and good enough to be fully confident of the justice of the Juche cause, the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is one of the great successes made by us in our recent Korean visit that we got a more profound understanding of the Juche idea, the Songun idea and the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is a developed beautiful country and Pyongyang, in particular, is a capital city kept in perfect order. All the monumental edifices were built on a high level. In a word, the DPRK is a great country where the Juche idea has been fully embodied.

Emergency Appeal Released in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek, south Korea reportedly made public an emergency appeal on Sept. 7 denouncing the moves of the "government" and the "defense ministry" to remove dwelling houses from the zone designated for the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek.
 The "government" and the "defense ministry" are stepping up preparations for forcing the evacuation of houses, turning a deaf ear to the voices of various social strata demanding a stop to the evacuation scheme, the appeal said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nothing can justify the scheme of the "government" and the "defense ministry" to expand the U.S. war base in Phyongthaek by expelling its inhabitants who have engaged in farming all their life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the way of defending human rights, lives and peace to frustrate their moves to destroy villages and remove houses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only unity of the people can curb the evacuation scheme, the appeal noted, calling upon the people to gather in Phyongthaek so as to defend Taechu-ri and Todu-ri with their united strength.

Conclusion of "Free Trade Agreement" Flailed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The Agriculture, Stock-Breeding and Fishery Emergency Measure Committee for Opposing South Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement reportedly held a press conference in Seoul on Sept. 5 to promulgate the 3rd all-people meeting against the negotiation on concluding the agreement.
 At the conference speakers said that the meeting scheduled in November would be an all-people resistance against the conclusion of the south Korea-U.S. "Free Trade Agreement", stressing that peasants would take the lead in the struggle for the successful opening of the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release was read out at the conference. The release called for staging a million-man resistance across south Korea in November as great unity, a general uprising to check the conclusion of the agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Sept. 6 a candlelight cultural event for urging a stop to the 3rd negotiation on the conclusion of the agreement took place in areas around Kwanghwamun, Seoul, under the co-sponsorship of the Seoul Headquarters of the Movement for Checking the South Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the event speakers bitterly denounced the "government" for unilaterally holding the negotiation, disregarding the will of the people, calling upon all the people including workers and youth and students to rise up as one to frustrate the negotiation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the event the headquarters of the movement called a press conference in connection with its inauguration.

10th Executive Committee Meeting of IIJI Board of Directors Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The 10th meeting of the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors of the International Institute of the Juche Idea took place here on Sept. 10. 
 Present there were Director General Vishwanath and Secretary General Kenichi Ogami of the IIJI, Director General of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea Reggie Ranatunge, Secretary General of the Latin-American Institute of the Juche Idea Alva Chavez, Director General of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea Edmond Jouve, who are members of the Executive Committee of the Board of Directors of the IIJI. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some directors were present as observers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After reviewing the work carried out by the IIJI in the past period, the meeting discussed the orientation of the work for 2007 and questions concerning the amendment of rules of the IIJI. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was noted at the meeting that the IIJI had contributed to the cause of global independence by energetically conducting study and dissemination of the Juche idea with fervent zeal while boosting relations and cooperation with Juche idea study organizations of different levels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Comprehensively discussed at the meeting were the issues of vigorously carrying on the work for expanding and strengthening the Juche idea study organizations and inducing followers of the Juche idea and world people of broad strata to make planned visits to the DPRK, the homeland of Juche, invigorating exchanges, contacts and experience swapping among organizations and guiding all the Juche idea study organizations to bring a new turn in the study and dissemination of the Juche idea on the occasion of the significant Day of the Sun and the birthday of Kim Jong Il in 2007.

Veterinary, Anti-epizootic Campaign Brisk in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The veterinary and anti-epizootic campaign is gathering momentum in the DPRK in September and October, months of veterinary and anti-epizootic campaign.
 The Veterinary and Epizootic Prevention Department of the Ministry of Agriculture has notified a working plan to be done in the period to each provincial rural economy committee and veterinary and epizootic prevention center and officials of relevant institutions are properly carrying on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Central Veterinary and Epizootic Prevention Center is channeling efforts into producing preventive medicines for bird flu and other epizootic diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The center had already organized a short technical course for increasing the production of preventive medicines. And it is organizing the work of gathering medicinal herbs so as to manufacture various kinds of Koryo veterinary medicines in the winter period while supplying raw materials in time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also taking a through-going step to prevent various common diseases of domestic animals. And it is intensifying control over providing preventive medicines to the relevant units in time and vaccinating all the domestic animals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A work for checking epizootics and parasite of animals is being done throughout the country to take relevant treatment steps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Veterinary and epizootic prevention officials find themselves on the spot to conduct explanatory and propaganda activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a system of surveying the actual conditions of habitats of migrant birds including ponds, lakes, rivers, tidelands, paddy and non-paddy fields and grass fields and of informing the result has been established in every province, city and county to thoroughly prevent bird flue.

Unbreakable Faith of Korean People in Socialism
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The imperialists are committing the ideological and cultural infiltration in a more vicious way as the days go by in an attempt to impair the Korean people's faith in socialism.
 Since their start of the "Radio Free Asia" with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea as an object in the early of March 1997, the U.S. imperialists have squandered more than ten million US dollars only for Korean language broadcasting every year. Meanwhile, they have brought bourgeoisie publications and video and audio recordings into the DPRK through trade and foreign travelers to the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S.-led imperialists, however, miscalculate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people�fs faith in socialism is invariable as they have keenly experienced the validity of the socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea�fs is the people-centered socialism under which they are the master of everything and everything serves them and that develops by the united strength of the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Contrary to the capitalist society which meets the individualist greed of a handful of ruling quarters, the socialist system of the DPRK embodying the Juche idea is defending the demand of the working class in a most thorough-going way and realizing the demand of the popular masses of all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It provides the independent and creative life to the popular masses in all fields, political, economic and cultural. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having been the master of the political power, the Korean people enjoy a genuine political right and freedom and take a free part in the political life, glorifying their socio-political integrity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the DPRK where the social ownership over the means of production prevails, the working people are provided with the creative working life. They have long been freed from taxation and live a happy life thanks to the government's popular policies including free education and free medical service. They are not only the creator of the revolutionary culture but also enjoyer of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is inconceivable in the deformed material life, poor emotional and cultural life and reactionary political climate of the capitalist society where the jungle law governs and such social evils as immorality, corruption, murder and robbery are rampant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality of the countries where socialism was collapsed and capitalism restored clearly shows that there is no ideal society more superior to socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The more viciously the imperialists perpetrate their moves, the firmer the iron will of the Korean people to achieve the ultimate victory of the socialist cause becomes.

Kim Jong Il�fs Field Guidance to Construction of Kumya River Power Station
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the construction of the Kumya River Power Station.
 He was greeted on the spot by commanding officers of the unit of the Korean People's Army participating in the construction and leading officials of the Kumya River Hydro-Power Station Construction Office and the South Hamgyong Provincial Construction Corps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The builders of the power station are now stepping up the dam construction in real earnest after finishing the dam groundwork project through vigorous endeavors to implement the tasks given by Kim Jong Il when he was visiting the construction site in April of 2003. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the construction before a huge painting showing a panoramic view of the power station, he looked round the construction site. He acquainted himself in detail with the progress made in the project and said that the power station is under construction in a good place after being successfully designed to ensure its profitability. He was greatly satisfied to see the power station now under construction as one more asset of eternal value and a great structure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the successes made by the KPA unit, noting that it is a unit of merits as it has performed proud feats in the socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines for completing the construction earlier than scheduled, saying that the large Kumya River Hydro-Power Station is of weighty importance in realizing the country's electrification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to concentrate state efforts on the construction of the power station as it is a gigantic project, he called on the Cabinet and central institutions and the province to minutely organize the work for winding up the construction of the power station as planned and take thorough measures to supply materials and equipment needed for the project on a preferential basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite possible to complete the construction of the power station ahead of schedule if those involved in the project work hard with the same vim and vigor with which the servicepersons built the West Sea Barrage, which was very difficult and vast project for transforming nature, in a matter of a few years, thus working a world startling miracle, he noted, urging all the fields related to the construction to render positive support to those engaged in the project and the builders to continue displaying to the full the revolutionary soldier spirit, the revolutionary spirit of fortitude. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stressing the need to build the power station in such a manner as to win the admiration of posterity as it is a precious structure of eternal value to be handed down to the generations to come, he called for paying particular attention to ensuring the best quality in construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and Ri Je Gang and Ri Jae Il, first vice department directors of the C.C., the WPK.
